#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:4
msgid "Image Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:6
msgid ""
"Using an image proxy means that all requests for images made by "
"Mattermost clients will go through the proxy instead of contacting third-"
"party servers directly. This helps protect user privacy by preventing "
"third-party servers from tracking who views an image. This also prevents "
"the use of tracking pixels (invisible images that do the same thing "
"without the user even seeing an image)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:8
msgid ""
"Certain proxy servers also provide a layer of caching which can make "
"loading images faster and more reliable. This caching also helps preserve"
" posts by protecting them from dead images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:10
msgid ""
"When enabled, the image proxy needs to be publicly accessible to both the"
" Mattermost client and server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:12
msgid ""
"Mattermost clients will use the image proxy to load all external images. "
"The Mattermost server will use the image proxy when possible, but will "
"not use it when requesting content that may not be an image, such as for "
"`image previews of plaintext URLs <https://github.com/mattermost"
"/mattermost-server/issues/11857>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:14
msgid ""
"An image proxy can be configured in **System Console > Environment > "
"Image Proxy** (or **System Console < Files > Storage** in versions prior "
"to 5.12)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:17
msgid "Local Image Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:19
msgid ""
"The local image proxy is available as part of the Mattermost server "
"deployment. When using the local image proxy, images are served to "
"clients through the server which helps anonymize users. If SSL is enabled"
" on the server, it provides a secure connection. This method does not "
"offer any caching behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:22
msgid ""
"With the local image proxy enabled, requests for images hosted on the "
"local network are now affected by the "
"``AllowUntrustedInternalConnections`` setting. See `documentation "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-settings.html#allow-"
"untrusted-internal-connections-to>`_ for more information or if you are "
"seeing unintentionally blocked images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:27
msgid "atmos/camo Image Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:29
msgid ""
"The `atmos/camo <https://github.com/atmos/camo>`_ image proxy is a "
"standalone image proxy that can be deployed separately from the "
"Mattermost server. It provides additional configuration options over the "
"built-in image proxy, and it can also be used if isolation between the "
"Mattermost server and image proxy is desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/image-proxy.rst:31
msgid ""
"Once you've deployed an ``atmos/camo`` (https://github.com/atmos/camo) "
"instance, you must specify the **Remote Image Proxy URL** and **Remote "
"Image Proxy Options** settings. The **Remote Image Proxy Options** should"
" be set to the image proxy's shared key which is specified with the "
"``CAMO_KEY`` environment variable used when setting up the image proxy."
msgstr ""

